section#one.wrapper.style2
  .inner
    .grid-style
      div
        .box
          .image.fit
            img(src='../../static/images/OpenRGB_Hardware_Sync_Plugin.webp' alt='OpenRGB Hardware Sync Plugin')
          .content
            header.align-center
              p Visualize system statistics with RGB
              h2 OpenRGB Hardware Sync Plugin
            p
              | Want to keep an eye on your CPU and GPU temperatures while you&apos;re in game? The Hardware
              | Sync Plugin will let you know if your temperatures are too high by changing the color of
              | your RGB. Many more system parameters are supported as well, and multiple devices can
              | indicate multiple measurements.
            header#pl.align-center
              a(href='https://gitlab.com/OpenRGBDevelopers/OpenRGBHardwareSyncPlugin')
                | GitLab
                | (Source)
      div
        .box
          .image.fit
            img(src='../../static/images/OpenRGB_Fan_Plugin.webp' alt='OpenRGB Fan Sync Plugin')
          .content
            header.align-center
              p Integrate fan control into OpenRGB
              h2 OpenRGB Fan Sync Plugin
            p
              | Controlling all your RGB in one place is great, but what about your fan speeds? The Fan
              | Sync Plugin takes care of that. Using the same backend as the Hardware Sync Plugin, the
              | Fan Sync Plugin lets you map one or more system parameters to control fan speeds,
              | including custom fan curves.
            header#pl.align-center
              a(href='https://gitlab.com/ShadyNawara/openrgbfansyncplugin') GitLab (Source)
